# Competency question: "Which norms does one persona of an agent express
# that a sibling persona does not — is the 'same principia, different
# registers' invariant holding?"
# Expected over instance data: rows only where an agent's personas DIVERGE
# in their expressed norm sets — one row per persona × norm (the sibling
# that lacks it stays in the WHERE, out of the projection, so 3+ personas
# don't fan out duplicate rows). Deliberately a QUERY, not a shape (#355,
# EPIC #348): divergence is legal (Principle 9) — the query makes it
# visible rather than forbidden. Over the bare ontology this returns no
# rows; the wellformed fixture (same tier-1 norm on both personas) returns
# none either, which IS the invariant holding.

PREFIX purrdf: <https://blackcatinformatics.ca/purrdf/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?agent ?persona ?norm WHERE {
    ?persona a purrdf:Persona ; purrdf:personaBearer ?agent ; purrdf:expressesNorm ?norm .
    ?sibling a purrdf:Persona ; purrdf:personaBearer ?agent .
    FILTER(?persona != ?sibling)
    FILTER NOT EXISTS { ?sibling purrdf:expressesNorm ?norm . }
}
ORDER BY ?agent ?persona ?norm
